# AI & Patrol Behavior System

Read `docs/AI_Patrol_Behavior_Spec.md` before making any changes.

## Core Design Decisions
- State machine: IDLE (wander) → PURSUE → ENGAGE → IDLE
- AI produces physics inputs, not direct movement — same pipeline as the player
- AI ships obey the same thruster budget, angular inertia, and drag as the player
- No physics cheating: AI cannot exceed max_speed, turn instantly, or teleport
- `AIController.gd` is attached only to AI ships — the player ship never has one
- Behavior profiles in `data/ai_profiles.json` — one entry per behavior archetype

## PerformanceMonitor Metrics (use exactly these strings)
- `AIController.state_updates` — wrap the full state machine update per ship
- `AIController.active_count` — set_count each frame (from scene manager or spawner)

## Key Classes & Components
- `AIController.gd` — state machine, decision logic, produces `ai_forward_input`, `ai_strafe_input`, `ai_aim_target`
- `DetectionArea` (Area2D child of the ship) — circle trigger for player detection

## Interface — AI Inputs to Ship
```gdscript
# AIController sets these; Ship.gd reads them in _physics_process
var ai_forward_input: float = 0.0     # -1.0 to 1.0
var ai_strafe_input: float = 0.0      # -1.0 to 1.0
var ai_aim_target: Vector2 = Vector2.ZERO
var ai_fire_primary: bool = false
```

## GameEventBus Signals (emit on every state transition)
- `ai_state_changed` — `{ ship_id: int, old_state: String, new_state: String }`
- `ai_target_acquired` — `{ ship_id: int, target_id: int }`
- `ai_target_lost` — `{ ship_id: int }`

## Watch Out For
- Leash range is measured from `_spawn_position`, not from the player detection point
- `_spawn_position` is set in `_ready()` from `global_position` — do NOT update it
- Circle direction (clockwise or CCW) is chosen on entering ENGAGE and held until exit
- `aim_accuracy` (0–1) in the behavior profile is the primary difficulty knob
- Never call `move_and_slide()` from AIController — the AI feeds inputs to Ship, Ship moves
- All tuning values (ranges, thrust fractions, aim accuracy) come from `ai_profiles.json`
